The ratio of merchantable to total aboveground biomass increases with diameter for all three methods. The ratios from CRM and Jenkins’ equations follow the same trajectory with little variation by softwood species trees across diameter classes (fig. 1). In fact, the component ratios are the same within the group containing all softwood species and within the group containing all hardwood species for a given diameter using the CRM approach (appendix). Conversely, the ratio changes significantly among species across diameter groups with regional equations.
